abstract.value: The Tamiment Playhouse was a summer theater at Camp Tamiment which from 1921-1965 was an educational and recreational summer resort (originally) for socialists near Bushkill, Pa. The TPH became a preeminent workshop for theater, dance, film, and television and included actors such as: Danny Kaye, Bea Arthur, Imogene Coca, and Carol Burnett; directors: Max Liebman, Herb Ross, and Joe Layton; choreographer: Jerome Robbins; and writers: Woody Allen and Neil Simon. The collection includes: scores, scripts, clippings, correspondence, ephemera, and casefiles for interviews with TPH alumni.

p.value: Published citations should take the following form: <lb/><lb/>Identification of item, date; Tamiment Playhouse Records; TAM 107; box number; folder number; <lb/>Tamiment Library/Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives <lb/>Elmer Holmes Bobst Library <lb/>70 Washington Square South <lb/>New York, NY 10012, New York University Libraries.

After the Tamiment Playhouse records were donated to NYU in 1983, the archive collected additional photographs, playbills, music scores and other memorbilia to augment the collection. A number of small donations were made at this time.
<emph render="bold">NOTE:</emph> this collection is stored offsite and advance notice is required for its use.
